  "texts": [
    "These machine-learning techniques endow computers with the capacity to learn from data, enabling them to proactively anticipate future outcomes [49].",
    "Jordan and Mitchell [50,51] assert that within the realm of AI, Machine Learning has evolved into a viable option for crafting valuable tools to tackle an array of challenges.",
    "Illustratively, as elucidated by [35], in education management, various pivotal tasks such as predicting student enrollment, evaluating teacher and student performance, forecasting student grade point averages, and other pertinent aspects employ prevalent soft computing techniques [48], which encompass fuzzy logic [32], neural networks [43], and genetic algorithms [40].The integration of computers into education for instructional content dissemination is recognized as computerbased education (CBE) [52].",
    "Before the AI era, Computer-Based Education systems were tools operating on local computers or the Internet, addressing issues like student modeling, adaptation, and personalization [47,53].",
    "The advent of the Internet ushered in a new era, witnessing the emergence of web-based educational tools like e-learning platforms [54]."
